<div style="top: 18px; left: 24px; width: auto; height: auto; background: none repeat scroll 0% 0% transparent; pointer-events: none;" id="obj-29" class="box clickable"><span><h1>
  Welcome to Meldbox!
</h1>
You are probably new so lets begin ...
<br>
<br>
<br>
Start by adding a Meldbox.
<br>
<br>Right-click somewhere right of this text and choose "Add a Meldbox"
<br>
<br>
You will see that it is now selected.
<br>
<br>
If it becomes deselected simply left-click on it to select.
<br>
<br>
Click into the "mBox Inner HTML" area on the left.
<br>
<br>
Type 
<span class="mb-instruction">
  &lt;h2&gt;Hello World&lt;/h2&gt;
</span> and press Ctrl + Enter.
<br>
<br>
Now right-click the Meldbox and select "Fit to content"
<br>
<br>
Next, click into the "mBox CSS Style" area on the left while the Meldbox is still selected.
<br>
<br>
On a new line, enter   
<span class="mb-instruction">background: none;</span>
then press Ctrl + Enter.
<br>
<br>
Left-click and drag your new Meldbox in place.
<br>
<br>
Up top, hover over File, click Save. Or you can press Ctrl + S.
<br>
<br>
Congratulations! You have made your first Meldbox.</span></div><style id="681e309d9bcf5c465c8eed75c384dda7-css-lib-data" data-desc="tutorial.css" type="text/css" class="css-lib" scoped="scoped">.mb-instruction {
	font-family: Courier;
	font-style: italic;
	font-weight: bold;
}</style><style id="canvas-alignment-style"> #design-area { float: right; height: 1500px; } #design-canvas { left: -1023px; } </style>